ćwiczenie 1
Wstaw formy skrócone.
1 She will come.
2 I will pay in cash.
3 They will not sing.
4 We will help.
5 He will not run.
6 You will be late.
She [...] come.
I [...] pay in cash.
They [...] sing.
We [...] help.
He [...] run.
You [...] be late.
1 'll
2 'll 4 'll
3 won't 5 won't
6 'll

ćwiczenie 2
Ułóż pytanie i odpowiedz na nie.
1 He / not come / to work today.
2 She / not cook / a meal today.
3 They / not go out / tonight.
4 She / not visit / them tonight.
5 I / not study / tonight.
6 He / not sing / tonight.
1 A: He won't come to work today
  B: Will he come to work tomorrow, then?
2 A: She won't cook a meal today.
  B: Will she cook a meal tomorrow, then?
3 A: They won't go out tonight
  B: Will they go out tomorrow night, then?
4 A: She won't visit them tonight
  B: Will she visit them tomorrow night, then?
5 A: I won't study tonight
  B: Will you study tomorrow night, then?
6 A: He won't sing tonight
  B: Will he sing tomorrow night, then?

Czasu Future Simple używamy:
1) Mówiąc o czymś, co wydarzy się w bliżej nieokreślonym czasie w przyszłości.
Np. We'll travel around the world one day.
- Pewnego dnia będziemy podróżować po świecie.
2) gdy przewidujemy, że coś się wydarzy w przyszłości.
Np You'll be a great computer operator one day -
Pewnego dnia będziesz świetnie obsługiwał komputer.
3) by kogoś ostrzec lub by wyrazić groźbę.
Np. Be quiet or I'll send you out. - Bądź cicho
alba cię wyrzucę,
4) by wyrazić obietnicę lub spontaniczną decyzję.
   Np I'll buy you this ring.
   - Kupię ci ten pierścionek.

z czasownikami
hope - miec nadzieję,
think - mysleć,
believe - uważać,
expect- oczekiwać itp.,
z wyrażeniami
I'm sure Jestem pewny,
I'm afraid - Obawiam się,
oraz z przysłówkami
probably- prawdopodobnie,
perhaps - być może itp.,
gdy uważamy jakieś przyszłe zdarzenie za pewne lub prawdopodobne.
Np. I hope he will pass his exams. - Mam nadzieję, że on zda egzaminy.
Perhaps I'll see her tonight. - Być może zobaczę się z nią dziś wieczorem.

W zdaniach w czasie Future Simple używamy następujących określeń czasu:
tomorrow - jutro,
the day after tomorrow - pojutrze,
next week - w przyszłym tygodniu,
next month - w przyszłym miesiącu,
next year - w przyszłym roku,
tonight - dziś w nocy,
soon - wkrótce,
in a week - za tydzień,
in a month - za miesiąc,
in a year - za rok itp.

ćwiczenie 3
Wstaw will ('ll) lub will not (won't).
1 You are late. You [...] get there in time.
2 "The ice-cream is melting." "I [...] put it in the freezer."
3 Perhaps Tom [...] start looking for a better job.
4 I [...] be able to help you tomorrow
because I'm busy.
5 "We haven't got any milk." "I [...] buy some."
6 Put on your coat or you [...]  get cold.
7 I'm afraid I [...]  have time to go shopping
with you next Saturday.
8 I expect I [...] see Brenda at the party
the day after tomorrow.
9 It's Fay's birthday next week. I [...] send
her a birthday card.
10 Stuart is very tired. I think he [...] go to bed early tonight.
1 won't
2 will/ll
3 will
4 will not/won't
5 will/'11 8 will/II
6 will/II 9 will/II
7 will not/won't 10 will/II

ćwiczenie 4
wstaw podane czasowniki w czasie future simple. help, go, lend, order, take, show
I've lost my wallet.
I [...] you find it.
I've forgotten my umbrella.
I [...] you mine.
We haven't got any milk.
Never mind. I [...] and buy some.
The dog is ill.
I [...] it to the vet.
Have you got a new car?
Yes, I [...] it to you later.
I don't want to cook tonight.
OK. I [...] a pizza, then.
1 'll help
2 'II lend 4 'II take 6 'II order
3 'II go 5 'II show

ćwiczenie 5
Ułóż pytanie i przeczenie.
1 They will be back soon.
2 Tom will go to Africa next year.
3 She will visit us next Tuesday.
1 Will they be back soon? They won't be back soon.
2 Will Tom go to Africa next year?
Tom won't go to Africa next year.
3 Will she visit us next Tuesday?
She won't visit us next Tuesday.


W krótkich odpowiedziach w czasie Future Simple używamy tylko Yes/No, zaimka osobowego oraz czasownika posiłkowego will/won't.
Nie powtarzamy pozostałych elementów pytania.
Will you be back in an hour? Yes, I will/No, I won't.
Will you ... ? Yes, I/we will. No, I/we won't
Will he/she/it .. .? Yes, he/she/it will. No, he/she/it won't
Will they .. .? Yes , they will. No, they won't

ćwiczenie 6
uzupełnij krótkie odpowiedzi.
1 Will they go camping next week?
Yes, [...]
2 Will Tom buy a car next year? No, [...]
3 Will Fiona go to a concert tonight? No, [...]
4 Will the children decorate the cake? Yes, [...]
5 Will Mother be back in an hour? No, [...]
6 Will Peter call Kate tonight? Yes, [...]
7 Will you help m e fix the TV? No, [...]
1 Yes, they will.
2 he won't. 5 she won't.
3 she won't. 6 he will.
4 they will. 7 I won't.